metadata.name: atilla.eth genesis
metadata.description:
In the beginning... there was nothing.

But even nothing must be described by something.

For imperatives to be given by someone, the rules, or the parameters, of nothing, must exist.

It is far easier to accept that nothing can eventually exist, caused of something. Causality implied. Nevertheless with such clear contradiction, it is convincing to say that nothing never existed.

At least not so far, and not in the beginning.
